A man killed by Bomet Governor Isaac Rutto's vehicle will be buried in his Olgumi home, Kajiado county, tomorrow. Harrison Tapasiany was killed on Tuesday evening on the Narok-Mai Mahiu highway a few kilometres from Suswa trading centre.Witnesses said he was crossing the road after alighting from a matatu.The matatu driver sped off towards Mai Mahiu trading centre after the accident.Rutto was heading to Nairobi from Bomet to appear before the Senate on Wednesday morning. The burial arrangements are going on and we expect the governor to attend. We are happy with him because he has been concerned since the incident occurred and he even met Tapasiany' family in Nairobi, said a close family member.